Inputs\: tableData - The list to generate the table from. columnDelimiter - A delimiter that separates columns in the tableData. rowDelimiter - A delimiter that separates the rows in tableData. Returns\: An html formatted table. Responses\: success - The operation was successful. failure - Something went wrong. 4813c9b9-5440-44cb-9e3e-655aa3e1de85.90a29fa5-9ef9-460f-91c7-6618df8f8124.prompt=Notification option\: 4813c9b9-5440-44cb-9e3e-655aa3e1de85.94276071-3749-4e11-b37a-ae074ba84929.description=
gets the DN of the root domain in active directory.

Inputs\:
host - An active directory domain controller.
altuser - The user to authenticate to host as.
altpassword - The password for altuser.

Responses\:
success - DN retrieved successfully.
failure - Unable to retrieve DN.
4813c9b9-5440-44cb-9e3e-655aa3e1de85.957d5722-92cb-4494-9f93-2e95a273282c.description=Allows a user to select how they should be notified of the outcome of a flow, and shows them a message in that way. Inputs\: notifydata - The message to notify the user of. notifyMethod - The method of notification (file, email, display). subject - This is a description of what the notification is about. destination - for files, the file to write to, for emails the email to send to. notificationServer - If the specified method send the notifydata to a server, this is the name of the server to notify (i.e. an email server) from - This is the originator of the message (email from address). sourceServer - Some integrations use a multi-level server architecture for processing tickets, this is the name of a mid-tier server in such an architecture. serverPort - The port the service to notify on the server is running on. username - A username to use when authenticating to a notification method requiring authentication. password - The password for username. Responses\: success - The user was notified. failure - Notification failed. 4813c9b9-5440-44cb-9e3e-655aa3e1de85.9dce4247-5f1d-4d2b-947c-340fce9f3418.prompt=Notification option\: 4813c9b9-5440-44cb-9e3e-655aa3e1de85.description=
Finds all users who have not logged in recently.

Inputs\:
    host - A domain controller to enumerate all domain controllers from
    DN - The Distinguished Name of the Organization Unit containing the users to be reviewed
    username - Username to use for LDAP queries
    password - Password to use for LDAP queries
    daysOld - The maximum number of days passed since the user logged in, in order to still be considered active
    notifyMethod - How to notify the user of the results of the flow

Responses\:
    success - No inactive users were found
    diagnosed - Inactive users were found
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully

Results\: 
    Displays a summary of the flow's results
